The former chief Brexit negotiator, who resigned in December, said he is "supportive" of Jacob Rees-Mogg's decision to delay the border checks on goods entering Britain from the EU. Mr Rees-Mogg, the recently appointed Brexit minister, is considering the move to prevent what industry has warned would be a supply chain disaster. Lord Frost said: "I predicted it would be necessary and I am fully supportive of Jacob Rees-Mogg in pushing it. But... we should end the fiction of a delay. Stop pretending we must do what the EU does, and get right such limited controls as we do need." FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...